Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In addition to this new reported event, during 2019 Russia also reported 3 events of classical swine fever (CSF); the affected population in all these outbreaks was wild boar. The situation for each of these CSF events is as follows:

1. Event started February 2019; one outbreak reported, and the event was resolved. See event summary and updated map: https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=29669.

2. Event started July 2019; one outbreak reported, and the event was resolved. See event summary and updated map: https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=31411.

3. Event started August 2019; one outbreak reported, and the event was resolved. See event summary and updated map: https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=31835. - Mod.CRD

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map:
Amur Oblast, Russia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6846876,463]
